A tortoise is a land-dwelling reptile known for its long lifespan, which can range from 80 to 150 years or more, and a diet primarily of plants. These reptiles are distinct from turtles as they exclusively live on land, have high-domed shells, and sturdier, column-like legs. Choosing this pet is a long-term commitment!
